# Frontend Production Environment Configuration
# Used by Vercel deployment
# 
# IMPORTANT: Set these variables in Vercel Dashboard:
# Settings → Environment Variables
#
# Do NOT commit actual values to Git!
# Use Vercel's secure environment variable management

# ================================
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT SETTINGS
# ================================

# ── Backend API Configuration ──────────────────────────
# Set this to your Render backend URL
# Example: https://physiobook-api-jvye.onrender.com
VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://physiobook-api-jvye.onrender.com

# ── Supabase Configuration (Optional) ───────────────
# Only needed if using Supabase real-time features
# Get these from: https://app.supabase.com/project/_/settings/api
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# ── Analytics (Optional) ────────────────────────────
# Add your analytics key if needed
# VITE_ANALYTICS_KEY=your-key-here

# ================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ================================
#
# 1. Backend URL MUST be accessible from the browser
#    - Check Render deployment is running
#    - Verify CORS origins include your Vercel domain
#
# 2. All VITE_ prefixed variables are exposed to the browser
#    - Do NOT put secrets here
#    - Secrets stay in backend environment variables
#
# 3. Vercel will automatically load these variables
#    - Set them in Vercel Dashboard
#    - No need to set them in .env.production
#
# 4. Local Development: Use .env.local instead
#    - This file is for production reference only
